title: NLCS has its largest television audience since 2010
text:
NL Championship Series has its largest television audience since 2010 THE ASSOCIATED PRESS First Posted: October 22, 2015 - 3:00 pmLast Updated: October 22, 2015 - 3:00 pm We also have more stories about: (click the phrases to see a list) 
Subjects: Men's sports (2326) 

NEW YORK — The NL Championship Series had its largest television audience since 2010 despite lasting just four games. 
The New York Mets' sweep of the Chicago Cubs in a matchup of big-market teams averaged 7.9 million viewers on TBS. The network said Thursday that was the most since the six-game Giants-Phillies series five years ago on Fox. 
The audience was up 55 percent from last year's four-game ALCS on TBS between the small-market Royals and Orioles.
